(
'SEO for Next.js Applications',
'nextjs-seo-best-practices',
'How to implement proper SEO in Next.js apps using structured metadata, server rendering, and indexing strategies to improve Google rankings and organic traffic.',
'{
 "blocks":[
   {"type":"heading","level":2,"text":"Why SEO Matters for Next.js Applications"},
   {"type":"paragraph","text":"Search engine optimization is essential for modern web applications that rely on discoverability. Next.js provides built-in tools that make SEO implementation significantly easier compared to traditional client-side React applications."},
   {"type":"paragraph","text":"Using server-side rendering and static generation ensures that search engine crawlers can properly read page content without executing JavaScript."},
   {"type":"heading","level":2,"text":"Core SEO Techniques"},
   {"type":"list","items":[
     "Use the Next.js Metadata API for title and meta descriptions.",
     "Implement structured data for better search visibility.",
     "Optimize images and assets to improve page speed.",
     "Use semantic HTML and accessible markup."
   ]}
 ]
}',
'https://placehold.co/1200x630/0f172a/38bdf8?text=Next.js+SEO',
NULL,
NULL,
'published',
'2026-05-24',
'SEO for Next.js Applications | Next.js Guide',
'Learn how to implement proper SEO strategies in Next.js applications using server rendering, metadata, and performance optimization.'
),

(
'Git Workflow Best Practices',
'git-workflow-best-practices',
'How poor Git practices cause merge conflicts, lost commits, and broken deployments — and how to manage branches, commits, and collaboration effectively.',
'{
 "blocks":[
   {"type":"heading","level":2,"text":"Why Git Workflow Matters"},
   {"type":"paragraph","text":"Git is the backbone of modern software collaboration. Poor Git habits can quickly lead to merge conflicts, lost work, and unstable releases."},
   {"type":"paragraph","text":"A structured workflow ensures that teams collaborate smoothly and maintain a clear history of changes."},
   {"type":"heading","level":2,"text":"Best Practices"},
   {"type":"list","items":[
     "Use feature branches for isolated development.",
     "Write clear and descriptive commit messages.",
     "Keep pull requests small and focused.",
     "Rebase when appropriate to maintain clean history."
   ]}
 ]
}',
'https://placehold.co/1200x630/111827/60a5fa?text=Git+Workflow',
NULL,
NULL,
'published',
'2026-05-17',
'Git Workflow Best Practices | Developer Guide',
'Learn how effective Git workflows prevent merge conflicts and improve collaboration across development teams.'
),

(
'Tailwind CSS Performance: Optimizing Bundle Size and Build Times',
'tailwind-css-performance-optimization',
'How to prevent Tailwind CSS from bloating your bundle size and maintain fast compile times in large React applications.',
'{
 "blocks":[
   {"type":"heading","level":2,"text":"Understanding Tailwind Performance"},
   {"type":"paragraph","text":"Tailwind CSS generates utility classes that can potentially grow large if not configured properly."},
   {"type":"paragraph","text":"Using proper content configuration ensures that only the classes used in your project are included in the final build."},
   {"type":"heading","level":2,"text":"Optimization Techniques"},
   {"type":"list","items":[
     "Enable content scanning for unused classes.",
     "Avoid unnecessary dynamic class generation.",
     "Split large UI components into smaller modules.",
     "Use production build mode for purging unused CSS."
   ]}
 ]
}',
'https://placehold.co/1200x630/0f172a/22c55e?text=Tailwind+Performance',
NULL,
NULL,
'published',
'2026-05-10',
'Tailwind CSS Performance Optimization | React Guide',
'Learn how to reduce Tailwind CSS bundle size and improve build performance in large React applications.'
),

